HEADWORD: Hexagon
<hw>Hex"a*gon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hexagonum</ets>, Gr. <?/ six-cornered; <grk>"e`x</grk> six (akin to
E. <ets>six</ets>) + <?/ angle.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A plane
figure of six angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Regular hexagon</b></col>, <cd>a hexagon in which the
angles are all equal, and the sides are also all equal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hexagonal</ent>⟦br⟧
